        questionPt: "Quais são os requisitos regulatórios mais recentes do Banco Central para remessas internacionais?",
        answerEn: "The 2025–2026 regulatory framework from Banco Central do Brasil (BCB) reflects a deliberate liberalization designed to increase competition and reduce costs. Key requirements as of 2026: (1) Authorized operators: All institutions facilitating international transfers must hold either a BCB banking license (Type B or above) or an Instituição de Pagamento (IP) license with FX authorization. Using unlicensed services is illegal and offers no consumer protection. (2) Reporting thresholds: Transfers above R$10,000 per transaction are automatically reported to BCB's SISBACEN system. Monthly cumulative transfers above R$100,000 by an individual trigger enhanced due diligence reviews. (3) AML/CFT compliance: All licensed operators must comply with Brazil's Anti-Money Laundering Law (Law 9.613/98, updated 2022) and FATF recommendations. Customer identity verification (KYC) is mandatory for all transfers. (4) IOF rates: Personal remittances are taxed at 0.38% IOF. Some tourism-related FX transactions carry higher rates. Business transfers for trade purposes may qualify for reduced rates. (5) Digital reporting: The new 2026 framework replaced paper-based filings with electronic submissions through SISBACEN for business transfers above R$50,000. (6) Consumer rights: BCB's Resolução 4.935 guarantees the right to receive a full fee and rate disclosure before executing any transfer, and the right to cancel within the legally defined window.",
        answerZh: "巴西中央银行（BCB）2025-2026年监管框架反映了一种蓄意的自由化方向，旨在增加竞争并降低成本。截至2026年的主要要求：(1) 授权运营商：所有促进国际转账的机构必须持有BCB银行牌照（B型或以上）或持有外汇授权的支付机构（IP）牌照。使用无牌照服务属于违法行为，且不提供任何消费者保护。(2) 报告门槛：每笔超过10,000雷亚尔的转账会自动报告给BCB的SISBACEN系统。个人每月累计转账超过100,000雷亚尔将触发强化尽职调查审查。(3) 反洗钱/打击恐怖融资合规：所有持牌运营商必须遵守巴西反洗钱法（9.613/98法，2022年更新）和金融行动特别工作组建议。对所有转账强制执行客户身份核验（KYC）。(4) IOF税率：个人汇款征收0.38% IOF。部分旅游相关外汇交易税率较高。用于贸易目的的商业转账可能享受降低税率。(5) 数字报告：新的2026年框架将商业转账（超过50,000雷亚尔）的纸质申报替换为通过SISBACEN的电子提交。(6) 消费者权益：BCB的第4935号决议保障消费者在执行任何转账前获得完整费用和汇率披露的权利，以及在法定窗口期内取消的权利。",
        answerPt: "O framework regulatório 2025–2026 do Banco Central do Brasil (BCB) reflete uma liberalização deliberada projetada para aumentar a concorrência e reduzir custos. Principais requisitos em 2026: (1) Operadores autorizados: Todas as instituições que facilitam transferências internacionais devem ter licença bancária BCB (Tipo B ou superior) ou licença de Instituição de Pagamento (IP) com autorização FX. Usar serviços não licenciados é ilegal e não oferece proteção ao consumidor. (2) Limites de reporte: Transferências acima de R$10.000 por transação são automaticamente reportadas ao sistema SISBACEN do BCB. Transferências mensais acumuladas acima de R$100.000 por um indivíduo acionam revisões aprimoradas de due diligence. (3) Conformidade AML/CFT: Todos os operadores licenciados devem cumprir a Lei de Combate à Lavagem de Dinheiro do Brasil (Lei 9.613/98, atualizada em 2022) e as recomendações do GAFI. A verificação de identidade do cliente (KYC) é obrigatória para todas as transferências. (4) Taxas de IOF: Remessas pessoais são tributadas com 0,38% de IOF. (5) Reportes digitais: O novo framework de 2026 substituiu os arquivamentos em papel por submissões eletrônicas via SISBACEN para transferências comerciais acima de R$50.000. (6) Direitos do consumidor: A Resolução BCB 4.935 garante o direito de receber divulgação completa de taxas e câmbio antes de executar qualquer transferência."
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<section class="py-20 bg-white" id="faq">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-brazil-green/10 text-brazil-green text-sm font-semibold rounded-full mb-3">FAQ</span>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-brazil-blue mb-4">
        <span data-lang-content="en">Frequently Asked Questions</span>
        <span data-lang-content="zh">常见问题解答</span>
        <span data-lang-content="pt">Perguntas Frequentes</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <span data-lang-content="en">Everything you need to know about international remittances from Brazil — regulations, fees, timing, and more.</span>
        <span data-lang-content="zh">关于从巴西国际汇款您需要了解的一切——法规、费用、时间及更多内容。</span>
        <span data-lang-content="pt">Tudo o que você precisa saber sobre remessas internacionais do Brasil — regulamentações, taxas, prazos e mais.</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      {faqs.map((category, catIndex) => (
        <div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
            <span class="text-2xl">{category.icon}</span>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-brazil-blue">
              <span data-lang-content="en">{category.categoryEn}</span>
              <span data-lang-content="zh">{category.categoryZh}</span>
              <span data-lang-content="pt">{category.categoryPt}</span>
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            {category.questions.map((faq, qIndex) => (
              <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden" id={`faq-${catIndex}-${qIndex}`}>
                <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
                  <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800 text-sm sm:text-base">
                    <span data-lang-content="en">{faq.questionEn}</span>
                    <span data-lang-content="zh">{faq.questionZh}</span>
                    <span data-lang-content="pt">{faq.questionPt}</span>
                  </span>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brazil-green flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-2 border-t border-gray-100 bg-gray-50/50">
                  <div class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed">
                    <span data-lang-content="en">{faq.answerEn}</span>
                    <span data-lang-content="zh">{faq.answerZh}</span>
                    <span data-lang-content="pt">{faq.answerPt}</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
